I was having trouble understanding reduce() and recursion, so I wrote this article to explain it to myself (Hey, look! Recursion!). I hope you find it helpful too!
Given an array with nested arrays:
var arr = [1, [2], [3, [[4]]]]  We want to produce this:
var flat = [1, 2, 3, 4]  Using for loops and if statements Naively, and if we know the maximum number of nested arrays we&rsquo;ll encounter (in this example, 4), we can use for loops to iterate through each array item, and if statements to check if each item is in itself an array, and so on&hellip;
